===Enterprise products===
In 2007, Google launched [[Google Apps|Google Apps Premier Edition]], a version of Google Apps targeted primarily at the business user. It includes such extras as more disk space for e-mail, API access, and premium support, for a price of USD50 per user per year. ===Cell Phone operating system===
  +
On November 5th 2007 Google * [http://www.directtraffic.org/OnlineNews/Google_announces_Android_mobile_phone_platform,_not_Google_Phone_18343710.html announced] the details of it's Google Android cell phone operating system,which came as a surprise to many,who thought Google would release an actual cell phone. The cell phone companies who partnered with Google are Motorola, Intel, Qualcomm, LG, Samsung, and T-Mobile. On November 12th 2007 Google released the * [http://www.directtraffic.org/OnlineNews/Google_announces_Android_mobile_phone_platform,_not_Google_Phone_18343710.html software development kit] for it's open source cell phone operating system named [[Google Android]].
